content: Yes, in general, Rainbow Trout are known for being primarily carnivorous and often feed on other fish as a part of their diet. However, the exact proportion of fish in their diet can vary depending on the specific environment, availability of prey species, and the size of the Rainbow Trout itself. For example, larger, more mature Rainbow Trout are more likely to prey on fish than smaller or younger ones, and fish may make up a smaller proportion of the diet if non-fish prey species are more abundant or easier to catch.
